data.chText: 捐献，捐赠（尤指款或物）；捐助
data.enText: to give sth, especially money or goods, to help sb/sth

data.chText: 我们向地震基金捐赠了 5 000 英镑。
data.enText: We contributed £5 000 to the earthquake fund.

data.chText: 你愿意给我们的募捐捐款吗？
data.enText: Would you like to contribute to our collection?
to be one of the causes of sth

data.chText: 据说医务人员的玩忽职守是她死亡的原因之一。
data.enText: Medical negligence was said to have contributed to her death.

data.chText: 人为的失误可能是一个起作用的因素。
data.enText: Human error may have been a contributing factor .
to increase, improve or add to sth

data.chText: 移民在许多方面都对英国文化有所贡献。
data.enText: Immigrants have contributed to British culture in many ways.

data.chText: 此书对我们了解这门学科助益甚少。
data.enText: This book contributes little to our understanding of the subject.

data.chText: （为报纸、杂志、电台或电视节目）撰稿；（在会议或会谈期间）讲话，（尤指）发表意见
data.enText: to write things for a newspaper, magazine, or a radio or television programme; to speak during a meeting or conversation, especially to give your opinion

data.chText: 她给这家杂志撰写了一些稿件。
data.enText: She contributed a number of articles to the magazine.

data.chText: 他定期给《新科学家》杂志撰稿。
data.enText: He contributes regularly to the magazine ‘New Scientist’.

data.chText: 我们希望大家都能参与讨论。
data.enText: We hope everyone will contribute to the discussion.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 共同 + tribut 给予 + e → 共同给出 → 捐献

ex.chText: 我们向无家可归的地震幸存者捐献了一笔钱。
ex.enText: We contributed a sum of money to the homeless survivors of the earthquake.

synonyms.bx: 指捐赠钱款、提供帮助等，常和介词 to/towards 连用。

ex.chText: 当地民众排队给地震灾区捐款。
ex.enText: The local people lined up to donate money to the earthquake-hit area.

ex.chText: 他给慈善事业捐款非常慷慨。
ex.enText: He is lavish in donating money to charity.

synonyms.bx: 尤指向个人或组织捐赠钱款。

example: The city has to put up half the required amount
Her presence lends a certain cachet to the company
The music added a lot to the play
She brings a special atmosphere to our meetings
This adds a light note to the program
The use of computers in the classroom lead to better writing

value.def: If you contribute to something, you say or do things to help to make it successful.

example.ex: The three sons also contribute to the family business...
example.tran: 这3个儿子也为家族事业做出了贡献。

example.ex: I believe that each of us can contribute to the future of the world...
example.tran: 我相信我们每一个人都能够对世界的未来有所贡献。

example.ex: He believes he has something to contribute to a discussion concerning the uprising.
example.tran: 他认为自己能够为有关起义的讨论提供一些信息。

value.def: To contribute money or resources to something means to give money or resources to help pay for something or to help achieve a particular purpose.

example.ex: The US is contributing $4 billion in loans, credits and grants...
example.tran: 美国将提供40亿美元的信贷和赠款。

example.ex: They say they would like to contribute more to charity, but money is tight this year...
example.tran: 他们说他们很想捐献更多的钱支持慈善事业，但是今年的钱非常紧张。

example.ex: NATO officials agreed to contribute troops and equipment to such an operation if the UN Security Council asked for it.
example.tran: 北约官员同意可在联合国安理会要求的情况下派出部队并提供装备参加这样的军事行动。

example.ex: ...the largest net contributors to EU funds.
example.tran: 向欧盟基金净捐资额最大的捐助者

value.def: If something contributes to an event or situation, it is one of the causes of it.

example.ex: The report says design faults in both the vessels contributed to the tragedy...
example.tran: 报告说两艘船存在的设计缺陷也促成了这场悲剧的发生。

example.ex: Stress, both human and mechanical, may also be a contributing factor.
example.tran: 来自人的和机械方面的压力可能也是一个因素。

value.tran: 促成;促使；是导致…的原因之一

value.def: If you contribute to a magazine, newspaper, or book, you write things that are published in it.

example.ex: I was asked to contribute to a newspaper article making predictions for the new year...
example.tran: 我受邀为报纸撰写一篇文章，对新的一年进行预测。

example.ex: Frank Deford is a contributing editor for Vanity Fair magazine.
example.tran: 弗兰克·德福特是杂志《名利场》的特约编辑。

example.ex: Reporter Alan Nearn covers Central America and is a regular contributor to The New Yorker.
example.tran: 记者艾伦·尼恩负责在中美洲采访报道，定期向《纽约客》杂志投稿。

partsOfSpeech.dec: at 加强 + tribut 给予 + e →〔确定属性前要〕给出〔原因〕→ 归因于；属性
con 共同 + tribut 给予 + e → 共同给出 → 捐献
con 共同 + tribut 给予 + or 表人 → 贡献者
dis 分散 + tribut 给予 + e → 分开来给 → 分配；区分
re 回 + tribut 给予 + ion 表名词 → 给回去 → 报酬
tribut 给予 + ary …的 → 给予东西 → 进贡的
tribut 给予 + e → 赠品；赞扬
